00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.420
Home Showings: What to
Expect & How to Prepare

00:00:03.125 --> 00:00:06.384
To prepare the subject property for
showings, the home should be clean,

00:00:06.384 --> 00:00:08.664
welcoming, and ready to show at any time.

00:00:09.025 --> 00:00:13.064
Simple steps like tidy surfaces,
clear walkways, and good lighting help

00:00:13.114 --> 00:00:15.074
buyers see the home in its best light.

00:00:15.850 --> 00:00:18.500
All showings are coordinated
through the ShowingTime app.

00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:23.440
You will receive a showing request and
have the ability to approve or decline it.

00:00:23.990 --> 00:00:27.429
Once approved, the showing agent
is notified and can proceed.

00:00:28.249 --> 00:00:31.639
Please only decline when
absolutely necessary, as declined

00:00:31.639 --> 00:00:33.390
showings may not be rescheduled.

00:00:34.092 --> 00:00:38.222
Access for approved showings is provided
through a lockbox on the property.

00:00:38.672 --> 00:00:41.272
The showing agent will
use the lockbox to enter.

00:00:41.822 --> 00:00:44.972
Please note that you should not
be onsite during the showing.

00:00:45.862 --> 00:00:48.722
Pets must be removed or
secured for every showing.

00:00:49.302 --> 00:00:52.902
If pets are secured, they should
always be placed in the same location

00:00:52.902 --> 00:00:57.232
that was originally provided, as
this information is shared with every

00:00:57.232 --> 00:00:59.072
showing agent through ShowingTime.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.569
Keeping the home in consistent
showing condition helps maximize

00:01:03.630 --> 00:01:05.610
interest and opportunities.

00:01:07.159 --> 00:01:11.149
Please remember that you only get one
chance to make a first impression.

00:01:12.140 --> 00:01:15.539
Buyers often spend a short amount
of time in the home comparing it to

00:01:15.590 --> 00:01:19.430
others in the neighborhood, so it is
important that the beauty of the home

00:01:19.479 --> 00:01:23.950
and the features you enjoy most are
clearly highlighted during each showing.

